For any set $S$ of real numbers define a new set $f(S)$ by $f(S) = { frac(x, 3)
"divides" x in S } union { (x + 2)/3 divides x in S }$.

#set enum(numbering: "(a)")


+ Sketch, carefully, the set $f(f(f(I)))$, where $I$ is the interval $[0,
  1]$.
+ If $T$ is a bounded set such that $f(T) = T$, determine, _with
  proof_, whether $T$ can contain $frac(1, 2)$.
